    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.14-14b_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Aug. 6, 19<del>4</del><add>5</add>6</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This past Spring I was fortunate enough to hear your lecture at Cornell. In particular, I was deeply impressed by the Sioux prayer with which you closed your talk. It expresses pretty much my own feelings as well as these of a friend of mind who is <unclear>now</unclear> very far away. I should like very much to have this prayer serve as one of the links between us. I would
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.14-14b_0002"/>
                
                    be so grateful if you could send me a copy or two of the prayer. A return envelope is enclosed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Thanking you in advance,</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Gerda J. Lewis</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial" place="right margin"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.14-14b_0003"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14a</fw>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3Â¢
                    IN GOD WE TRUST
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Miss Gerda <hi rend="caps">J.</hi> Lewis</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>200 Eddy St.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Ithaca, <hi rend="caps">N.Y.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24.14-14b_0004"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">G.J.</hi> Lewis
                    200 Eddy St.
                    Ithaca, <hi rend="caps">N.Y.</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14b</fw>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    COLUMBIA, MO
                    AUG 6
                    6 30PM
                    1956
                </ab>
                <ab type="postmark">
                    ITHACA, N.Y.
                    AUG 6
                    9-PM
                    1956
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATE<unclear reason="missing"/> THREE 3 CENTS</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>Dpt. of English</del>      <add><hi rend="caps">RFD</hi> 6</add></addrLine>
